2026-03-20 22:16:38 | DEBUG    | src/search_service.py:300 | [Tavily] 原始响应: {'query': 'Philip Morris International Inc earnings revenue profit growth forecast', 'follow_up_questions': None, 'answer': None, 'images': [], 'results': [{'url': 'https://simplywall.st/stocks/us/food-beverage-tobacco/nyse-pm/philip-morris-international/future', 'title': 'Philip Morris International Future Growth - Simply Wall St', 'content': "Philip Morris International Inc.\n\nNYSE:PM Stock Report\n\nMarket Cap: US$295.5b\n\n# Philip Morris International Future Growth\n\n## Future criteria checks 2/6\n\nPhilip Morris International is forecast to grow earnings and revenue by 8.4% and 6.4% per annum respectively. EPS is expected to grow by 8.7% per annum. Return on equity is forecast to be 1315.7% in 3 years.\n\n## Key information\n\n8.4%\n\nEarnings growth rate\n\n8.66%\n\nEPS growth rate\n\n|  |  |\n --- |\n| Tobacco earnings growth | 7.6% |\n| Revenue growth rate | 6.4% |\n| Future return on equity | 1,315.67% |\n| Analyst coverage | Good |\n| Last updated | 19 Feb 2026 |\n\nGood\n\n## Recent future growth updates\n\n### Price target increased by 7.6% to US$194\n\n### Philip Morris International Inc. Reaffirms Earnings Guidance for the Full Year 2026 [...] Philip Morris International Inc. Just Recorded A 9.0% EPS Beat: Here's What Analysts Are Forecasting Next\n\n### First quarter 2025 earnings released: EPS: US$1.72 (vs US$1.38 in 1Q 2024)\n\n### Now 23% undervalued after recent price drop\n\n### Philip Morris International Inc. Provides Earnings Guidance for the Full Year 2025\n\n### What You Can Learn From Philip Morris International Inc.'s (NYSE:PM) P/E\n\nWhat You Can Learn From Philip Morris International Inc.'s (NYSE:PM) P/E\n\n### First quarter dividend of US$1.35 announced\n\n### Philip Morris International Declares Regular Quarterly Dividend, Payable on July 15, 2025\n\n### Philip Morris International Inc. Reaffirms Earnings Forecast for Full Year 2025 [...] ### Philip Morris International Inc. Provides Earnings Guidance for the Full Year 2025\n\n### Philip Morris International Inc. Urges U.S. Food and Drug Administration Advisory Committee to Recommend Continued Marketing of IQOS as Modified Risk Product\n\n### Now 21% undervalued after recent price drop\n\n### Second quarter dividend increased to US$1.47\n\n### Philip Morris International Inc Declares Regular Quarterly Dividend, Payable on October 20, 2025\n\n### Now 20% undervalued after recent price drop\n\n### Philip Morris International Inc. Reaffirms Earnings Guidance for the Full Year 2025\n\n### Now 20% undervalued after recent price drop\n\n### Philip Morris International Inc. Just Recorded A 9.0% EPS Beat: Here's What Analysts Are Forecasting Next", 'score': 0.9999076, 'raw_content': None}, {'url': 'https://www.morningstar.com/news/dow-jones/202602064776/philip-morris-posts-higher-4q-profit-revenue-forecasts-continued-growth', 'title': 'Philip Morris Posts Higher 4Q Profit, Revenue; Forecasts Continued ...', 'content': "Morningstar\n\n# Philip Morris Posts Higher 4Q Profit, Revenue; Forecasts Continued Growth\n\nBy Connor Hart\n\nPhilip Morris International logged higher profit and revenue in the fourth quarter, while forecasting continued growth for years to come.\n\nThe tobacco company--which sells cigarettes such as Marlboro and Parliament in overseas markets, as well as smokeless tobacco such as Zyn worldwide--posted operating income of $3.4 billion, up 3.5% from a year earlier. Earnings came in at $1.37 a share.\n\nStripping out certain one-time items, earnings were $1.70 a share. That was in line with analysts' expectations for adjusted earnings, according to FactSet.\n\nRevenue increased 6.8% to $10.36 billion, just below Wall Street views for $10.38 billion. [...] Total shipment volumes edged 0.1% higher to 193.8 billion units.\n\nChief Executive Jacek Olczak said 2025 marked the company's fifth consecutive year of volume growth, with results boosted by continued growth across its smoke-free business and operating margin expansion.\n\nFor the current quarter, the company expects adjusted earnings of $1.80 to $1.85 a share, compared with analyst views for $1.89 a share.\n\nLooking ahead, Philip Morris guided for earnings of $7.87 to $8.02 a share in 2026. On an adjusted basis, earnings are projected to come in between $8.38 and $8.53 a share. Analysts were looking for earnings of $8.01 a share, or $8.34 a share on an adjusted basis.\n\nThe forecast assumes net revenue growth of 5% to 7% for the year, as well as organic operating income growth of 7$ to 9%. [...] The company additionally disclosed its compounded annual growth targets through 2028, calling for a 6% to 8% increase for net revenues, an 8% to 10% increase for operating income, and a 9% to 11% increase for adjusted per-share earnings.\n\nWrite to Connor Hart at connor.hart@wsj.com\n\n(END) Dow Jones Newswires\n\nFebruary 06, 2026 07:53 ET (12:53 GMT)\n\nThe articles, information, and content displayed on this webpage may\ninclude materials prepared and provided by third parties. Such\nthird-party content is offered for informational purposes only and\nis not endorsed, reviewed, or verified by Morningstar.", 'score': 0.99990463, 'raw_content': None}, {'url': 'https://www.pmi.com/investor-relations/press-releases-and-events/2025-q4-and-full-year-results/', 'title': 'Philip Morris International Inc. 2025 Fourth-Quarter & Full-Year Results', 'content': 'Even more impressive is the smoke‑free adjusted gross profit contribution, which has essentially doubled in five years to 43% of total PMI.\n\nOur adjusted operating margin also returned to above 40% in 2025, as our transformation becomes increasingly profitable.\n\nThis enabled us to deliver +15% adjusted diluted earnings per share growth in dollar terms, which is the strongest growth since 2011, excluding the pandemic‑recovery year of 2021.\n\nWe continue to scale our global smoke‑free presence, reaching 106 markets at the end of 2025, with our performance fueled by the international business, which generated the vast majority of total PMI organic net revenue growth,led by smoke‑free products, with IQOS the core driver. [...] ’25 was another outstanding year for PMI.\n\nThe shift of adult smokers to better alternatives is a lasting structural movement, one that we continue to lead and from which we are generating strong, sustained growth.\n\nWe delivered our fifth consecutive year of positive volumes with rapid top‑line progress and significant margin expansion, generating strong value for our shareholders, including the largest dividend increase in over a decade.\n\nThe numbers show our progress.\n\nOur total net revenue reached over $40 billion in 2025, with 41.5%, or close to $17 billion, generated by our smoke‑free business.\n\n27 markets exceeded the 50% net revenue milestone in ’25, and in Q4 2025, the Europe region also surpassed 50%, making three of our four regional segments majority smoke‑free. [...] This includes an impressive acceleration in the fourth quarter, with a return to strong double‑digit growth in Italy and a very promising start in Taiwan, being just two examples of broad growth across geographies.\n\nThis performance also reflects the success of our multicategory strategy, with both ZYN, excluding Nordics, and VEEV more than doubling shipment volumes in international markets.\n\nIn the U.S., ZYN shipments grew strongly by +37%.\n\nOur strong brand offering, which includes high‑quality science‑backed products in all three smoke‑free product categories, allows us to better serve legal‑age consumers and enhance our financial performance.\n\nCombustibles delivered robust top‑ and bottom‑line performance.', 'score': 0.99986446, 'raw_content': None}, {'url': 'https://www.pmi.com/investor-relations/overview/', 'title': 'Investor Relations | PMI - Philip Morris International', 'content': 'Our adjusted operating margin also returned to above 40% in 2025, as our transformation becomes increasingly profitable.\n\nThis enabled us to deliver +15% adjusted diluted earnings per share growth in dollar terms, which is the strongest growth since 2011, excluding the pandemic‑recovery year of 2021.\n\nWe continue to scale our global smoke‑free presence, reaching 106 markets at the end of 2025, with our performance fueled by the international business, which generated the vast majority of total PMI organic net revenue growth,led by smoke‑free products, with IQOS the core driver. [...] We delivered our fifth consecutive year of positive volumes with rapid top‑line progress and significant margin expansion, generating strong value for our shareholders, including the largest dividend increase in over a decade.\n\nThe numbers show our progress.\n\nOur total net revenue reached over $40 billion in 2025, with 41.5%, or close to $17 billion, generated by our smoke‑free business.\n\n27 markets exceeded the 50% net revenue milestone in ’25, and in Q4 2025, the Europe region also surpassed 50%, making three of our four regional segments majority smoke‑free.\n\nEven more impressive is the smoke‑free adjusted gross profit contribution, which has essentially doubled in five years to 43% of total PMI.', 'score': 0.99978346, 'raw_content': None}, {'url': 'https://www.pmi.com/media-center/press-releases/press-details/?newsId=29566', 'title': 'Philip Morris International Reports 2025 Fourth-Quarter & Full-Year ...', 'content': 'Reported diluted EPS is forecast to be in a range of$7.87 to$8.02, at prevailing exchange rates, versus reported diluted EPS of$7.26 in 2025. Excluding a total 2026 adjustment of$0.51 per share, this forecast represents a projected increase of 11.1% to 13.1% versus adjusted diluted EPS of$7.54 in 2025. Also excluding a favorable currency impact of$0.27, at prevailing exchange rates, this forecast represents a projected increase of 7.5% to 9.5% versus adjusted diluted EPS of$7.54 in 2025, as outlined in the above table.\n\n2026 Full-Year Forecast Assumptions\n\nThis forecast assumes: [...] corey.henry@pmi.com\n\nFebruary 06, 2026\n\nPhilip Morris International Reports 2025 Fourth-Quarter & Full-Year Results\n\ndownload\n\nDelivers Full Year 2025 Reported Diluted EPS of$7.26compared to$4.52in 2024 and Adjusted Diluted EPS of$7.54, Representing Growth of 14.8%, and 14.2% on a Currency-Neutral Basis; Provides 2026 - 2028 Growth Targets\n\nSTAMFORD, CT--(BUSINESS WIRE)--Feb. 6, 2026--Regulatory News:\n\nPhilip Morris International Inc.(PMI) (NYSE: PM) today announces its 2025 fourth quarter results.1\n\n"_We achieved another remarkable year of results in 2025, with a fifth consecutive year of volume growth, net revenues surpassing_ _$40 billion_ _, including close to_ _$17 billion_ _from our smoke-free business, and very good operating margin expansion,"_ said Jacek Olczak, Group CEO PMI. [...] Smoke-free business (SFB):Our smoke-free business delivered a strong performance, with full-year shipment volumes up by 12.8%, net revenues growing by 15.0% (14.1% organically) and gross profit increasing by 20.3% (18.7% organically). Our smoke-free business accounted for 41.5% of our total net revenues, and nearly 43% of total gross profit (up by 2.8pp and 3.2pp respectively vs. full-year 2024). Our smoke-free products (SFP) are now available in 106 markets, with over 43 million estimated adult consumers (up by around 4.5 million versus December 2024). In the fourth quarter, we delivered 12.0% net revenue growth (8.6% organically), 12.2% gross profit growth (8.3% organically) while achieving a key milestone with over 50% of net revenues generated by the smoke-free business in 3 of our', 'score': 0.9997428, 'raw_content': None}, {'url': 'https://www.tikr.com/blog/with-25-returns-last-year-can-philip-morris-stock-keep-rising-in-2026', 'title': 'With 25% Returns Last Year, Can Philip Morris Stock Keep Rising in ...', 'content': 'According to consensus analyst estimates, revenue growth is in line with the 1 year historical rate of 7.3%, indicating the model assumes stable demand durability rather than acceleration, leaving limited buffer if smoke free momentum softens.\n\n### 2. Operating Margins: 40.7%\n\nPhilip Morris International has historically generated strong profitability, with a 1 year operating margin of 38.8% reflecting premium pricing, scale benefits, and declining cost intensity from smoke free products.\n\nCurrent margins are supported by mix shift toward higher margin smoke free categories and ongoing cost control, allowing operating margins to approach 40.7% despite continued commercial investment. [...] Assess whether Philip Morris stock’s current price already capitalizes its smoke-free transition by modeling cash flow scenarios on TIKR for free →\n\nPhilip Morris International Inc. (PM) generates revenue from cigarettes and smoke-free products across more than 100 markets, monetizing consumer demand through pricing power, scale, and a growing portfolio of reduced-risk alternatives.\n\nLast year, Philip Morris generated $41 billion in revenue and $27 billion in gross profit.\n\nMeanwhile, PM stock’s operating income reached $15 billion as margins recovered to 37% despite elevated investment.\n\nCurrent management is also extending its multi-year transition strategy. [...] ### Here’s what we used for PM stock:\n\n### 1. Revenue Growth: 7.3%\n\nPhilip Morris International has delivered consistent top line expansion as smoke free products offset cigarette volume decline, with 1 year revenue growth at 7.3% reflecting category mix improvement rather than cyclical rebound.\n\nCurrent execution is supported by smoke free volume growth in the low teens and pricing discipline, sustaining a 7.3% revenue growth outlook despite competitive pressure in nicotine pouches and heated tobacco.\n\nForward performance depends on maintaining smoke free adoption rates and pricing power, while regulatory friction, inventory normalization, or share losses would quickly compress revenue growth below modeled levels.', 'score': 0.99938333, 'raw_content': None}], 'response_time': 1.49, 'request_id': 'fa00cb1a-518f-4bdd-ab17-6764a5d83ca3'}
