es, in Ohio, Tennessee, Illinois and New Mexico and strategically continue to pursue other markets. Our competition consists of personal care service providers, home health providers, hospice providers, private caregivers, publicly held companies, privately held companies, privately held single-site agencies, hospital-based agencies, not-for-profit organizations, community-based organizations, managed care organizations and self-directed care programs. The Tennessee Quality Care acquisition accounted for $16.3 million of net service revenues and $3.0 million of operating income for the year ended December 31, 2023. In 2023, the Company recognized goodwill in the hospice and home health segments of $35.0 million and $44.3 million, respectively, related to the acquisition of Tennessee Quality Care and $0.6 million related to the acquisition of CareStaff in the personal care services segment. During the year ended December 31, 2023, the Company acquired indefinite-lived state licenses and a trade name of $7.6 million and $2.1 million, respectively, in its hospice segment related to the acquisition of Tennessee Quality Care.', 'score': 0.96003, 'raw_content': None, 'from_cache': True}, {'url': 'https://www.directorstalkinterviews.com/addus-homecare-corporation-adus-investor-outlook-with-a-36-potential-upside/4121243817', 'title': 'Addus HomeCare Corporation (ADUS): Investor Outlook With A 36 ...', 'content': 'With a market capitalization of $1.9 billion, Addus HomeCare provides vital services including personal care, hospice, and home health care, catering primarily to the elderly, chronically ill, and disabled individuals across the United States. Currently trading at $102.86, Addus HomeCare’s stock price is comfortably positioned within its 52-week range of $89.83 to $122.75. This growth is a testament to the company’s effectiveness in expanding its service offerings and capturing market share in a competitive industry. When considering valuation metrics, Addus HomeCare’s forward P/E ratio stands at 13.81, which could indicate a relatively attractive valuation for a company with its growth rate. Investors focusing on growth potential may find Addus HomeCare a worthy consideration for their portfolios, especially given its promising analyst ratings and strong revenue growth. ## RM Plc Makes Strategic Progress as Growth Plans Gather Pace, Singer Capital Markets. ## Finsbury Growth & Income Trust reports positive NAV growth of +3.1% and rising dividend. ## Spire Healthcare Group PLC (SPI.L) Stock Analysis: A 42% Potential Upside in the Medical Care Sector.', 'score': 0.95902, 'raw_content': None, 'from_cache': True}], 'response_time': 5.02, 'request_id': '14887f11-3ca8-46cd-9314-24e2fc263a15'}
