nology and oncology. [...] ## Financial Health Analysis\n\nAbbVie's financial health is underscored by its substantial revenue growth and profitability metrics. The company's revenue growth over the past three years stands at 20%, reflecting its strong market position. Despite a decline in earnings growth of 12.1% over the past year, AbbVie maintains a robust gross margin of 69.74% and an operating margin of 24.09%.\n\nOn the balance sheet front, AbbVie exhibits a current ratio of 0.72 and a quick ratio of 0.6, indicating potential liquidity constraints. The company's debt-to-equity ratio is notably negative at -26.02, suggesting a high level of leverage. However, its interest coverage ratio of 4.99 demonstrates its ability to meet interest obligations.", 'score': 0.8991304, 'raw_content': None}, {'url': 'https://www.zacks.com/stock/news/2829207/abbvie-beats-on-q4-earnings-stock-down-despite-upbeat-26-view', 'title': 'AbbVie Beats on Q4 Earnings, Stock Down Despite Upbeat ...', 'content': 'Analyst Blog\n\nFollow Author\n\n## Key Takeaways\n\nAbbVie Inc. (ABBV Quick QuoteABBV  -  Free Report) reported fourth-quarter 2025 adjusted EPS of $2.71, which beat the Zacks Consensus Estimate of $2.66. The reported figure also exceeded the company’s guidance of $2.61-$2.65 issued last month. Earnings rose more than 25% year over year.\n\nABBV’s revenues of $16.62 billion beat the Zacks Consensus Estimate of $16.36 billion. Sales rose 10.0% year over year on a reported basis and 9.5% on an operational basis. This reported figure also surpassed the company’s forecast of over $16.30 billion.', 'score': 0.85216236, 'raw_content': None}, {'url': 'https://www.nasdaq.com/articles/abbvie-guides-fy26-adj-eps-above-estimates-q4-results-top-estimates', 'title': 'AbbVie Guides FY26 Adj. EPS Above Estimates', 'content': "For fiscal 2026, AbbVie now projects adjusted earnings in a range of $14.37 to $14.57 per share, which excludes any impact from acquired IPR&D and milestones expense.\n\nOn average, 27 analysts polled expect the company to report earnings of $14.22 per share for the year. Analysts' estimates typically exclude special items.\n\nFor the fourth quarter, the company reported net earnings attributable to AbbVie of $1.82 billion or $1.02 per share, compared to $22 million or $0.02 per share in the prior-year quarter.\n\nExcluding items, adjusted earnings for the quarter was $2.71 per share, compared to $2.16 per share in the year-ago quarter.\n\nNet revenues for the quarter grew to $16.62 billion from $15.10 billion in the same quarter last year.", 'score': 0.8479807, 'raw_content': None}, {'url': 'https://www.pharmexec.com/view/abbvie-raises-2025-profit-forecast-increased-demand-immunology-treatments', 'title': 'AbbVie Raises 2025 Profit Forecast Following Increased Demand ...', 'content': '# What is AbbVie raising its 2025 profit forecast to?\n\nAbbVie is expected to raise its 2025 annual profit-per-share amount from between $10.38 and $10.58 to $10.61 and $10.65.1The raise comes as a reaction to the company’s quarterly sales, which reached $15.78 billion worldwide for the third quarter, a 9.1% increase on reported basis, and a 8.4% increase on an operational basis.2During the entire quarter, AbbVie noted that Skyrizi brought in sales upwards of $4.71 billion, which surpassed the previous estimates of $4.44 billion. Rinvoq sales also reached $2.18 billion, topping its estimates of $2.12 billion.1\n\n# What was AbbVie’s third quarter sales results? [...] Listen\n\n0:00 / 0:00\n\n### Key Takeaways\n\n AbbVie raised its 2025 profit forecast, driven by strong sales of Skyrizi and Rinvoq, exceeding Wall Street expectations.\n Q3 sales reached $15.78 billion, with Skyrizi and Rinvoq sales surpassing estimates, contributing to a 9.1% increase.\n AbbVie plans a $195 million investment in a new US manufacturing facility, part of a $10 billion decade-long investment strategy.\n The company aims to enhance biopharmaceutical innovation and expand US manufacturing capabilities, moving some operations from Europe and Asia.\n\nSHOW MORE\n\nThe change was driven by strong sales of Skyrizi and Rinvoq, and showcases robust growth and innovation in its portfolio.\n\nAdvertisement [...] Immunology portfolio: $7.8 billion, an increase of 11.9% on a reported basis, or 11.2% on an operational basis.\n Neuroscience portfolio: $2.8 billion, an increase of 20.2% on a reported basis, or 19.6% on an operational basis.\n Oncology portfolio: $1.6 billion, a decrease of 0.3% on a reported basis, or 1.3% on an operational basis.\n Aesthetics portfolio: $1.1billion, a decrease of 3.7% on a reported basis, or 4.2% on an operational basis.\n\nIn its press release, AbbVie listed additional key third quarter net revenue metrics, including the following:', 'score': 0.84707206, 'raw_content': None}, {'url': 'https://simplywall.st/stocks/us/pharmaceuticals-biotech/nyse-abbv/abbvie/past', 'title': 'AbbVie (NYSE:ABBV) - Earnings & Revenue Performance', 'content': "AbbVie Inc.\n\nNYSE:ABBV Stock Report\n\nMarket Cap: US$391.6b\n\n# AbbVie Past Earnings Performance\n\n## Past criteria checks 0/6\n\nAbbVie's earnings have been declining at an average annual rate of -16.3%, while the Biotechs industry saw earnings growing at 22.5% annually. Revenues have been growing at an average rate of 2.4% per year.\n\n## Key information\n\n-16.31%\n\nEarnings growth rate\n\n-16.52%\n\nEPS growth rate\n\n|  |  |\n --- |\n| Biotechs Industry Growth | 17.04% |\n| Revenue growth rate | 2.39% |\n| Return on equity | n/a |\n| Net Margin | 6.84% |\n| Last Earnings Update | 31 Dec 2025 |\n\n## Recent past performance updates\n\n### Full year 2025 earnings: EPS misses analyst expectations\n\n### AbbVie Inc. to Report Q4, 2025 Results on Feb 04, 2026 [...] | 30 Jun 22 | 57,349 | 12,569 | 11,988 | 6,551 |\n| 31 Mar 22 | 56,725 | 12,407 | 11,943 | 6,692 |\n| 31 Dec 21 | 56,197 | 11,468 | 11,872 | 6,820 |\n| 30 Sep 21 | 55,169 | 7,465 | 11,054 | 6,829 |\n| 30 Jun 21 |