2026-03-20 22:21:58 | DEBUG    | src/search_service.py:300 | [Tavily] 原始响应: {'query': 'Verizon Communications Inc. earnings revenue profit growth forecast', 'follow_up_questions': None, 'answer': None, 'images': [], 'results': [{'url': 'https://www.zacks.com/stock/news/2825893/verizon-communications-vz-surpasses-q4-earnings-and-revenue-estimates', 'title': 'Verizon Communications (VZ) Surpasses Q4 Earnings and ...', 'content': "This quarterly report represents an earnings surprise of +2.72%. A quarter ago, it was expected that this largest U.S. cellphone carrier would post earnings of $1.19 per share when it actually produced earnings of $1.21, delivering a surprise of +1.68%.\n\nOver the last four quarters, the company has surpassed consensus EPS estimates four times.\n\nVerizon, which belongs to the Zacks Wireless National industry, posted revenues of $36.38 billion for the quarter ended December 2025, surpassing the Zacks Consensus Estimate by 1.23%. This compares to year-ago revenues of $35.68 billion. The company has topped consensus revenue estimates three times over the last four quarters. [...] Array Digital Infrastructure (AD Quick QuoteAD  -  Free Report) , another stock in the same industry, has yet to report results for the quarter ended December 2025.\n\nThis wireless telecommunications service provider is expected to post quarterly earnings of $0.32 per share in its upcoming report, which represents a year-over-year change of +540%. The consensus EPS estimate for the quarter has remained unchanged over the last 30 days.\n\nArray Digital Infrastructure's revenues are expected to be $57.72 million, down 94.1% from the year-ago quarter.\n\n## Zacks' 7 Best Strong Buy Stocks (New Research Report)\n\nValued at $99, click below to receive our just-released report\npredicting the 7 stocks that will soar highest in the coming month.\n\n# Published in [...] It will be interesting to see how estimates for the coming quarters and the current fiscal year change in the days ahead. The current consensus EPS estimate is $1.19 on $34.01 billion in revenues for the coming quarter and $4.80 on $140.58 billion in revenues for the current fiscal year.\n\nInvestors should be mindful of the fact that the outlook for the industry can have a material impact on the performance of the stock as well. In terms of the Zacks Industry Rank, Wireless National is currently in the bottom 14% of the 250 plus Zacks industries. Our research shows that the top 50% of the Zacks-ranked industries outperform the bottom 50% by a factor of more than 2 to 1.", 'score': 0.9997818, 'raw_content': None}, {'url': 'https://www.investing.com/news/earnings/verizon-shares-rise-as-q4-results-and-2026-outlook-top-expectations-4475643', 'title': 'Verizon shares rise as Q4 results and 2026 outlook top expectations', 'content': 'The company posted adjusted earnings per share of $1.09 for the fourth quarter, surpassing the analyst estimate of $1.06. Revenue came in at $36.4 billion, above the consensus estimate of $36.1 billion. Verizon also delivered its highest quarterly total mobility and broadband volumes since 2019, with 616,000 postpaid phone net additions.\n\nVerizon\'s wireless service revenue reached $21.0 billion in the fourth quarter, up 1.1% YoY, while wireless equipment revenue increased 9.1% YoY to $8.2 billion. The company added 372,000 broadband subscribers during the quarter, including 319,000 fixed wireless access customers and 67,000 Fios internet additions. [...] # Verizon shares rise as Q4 results and 2026 outlook top expectations\n\nBy\n\nAuthorSam Boughedda\n\nEarnings\n\nPublished 01/30/2026, 06:41 AM\n\nVerizon shares rise as Q4 results and 2026 outlook top expectations\n\nView all comments (0)0\n\n&copy; Reuters.\n\n© Reuters.\n\nVZ-1.79%\n\nInvesting.com -- Verizon Communications Inc. (NYSE: VZ) reported fourth-quarter earnings and revenue that exceeded analyst expectations, while providing an upbeat outlook for 2026 that signals the beginning of a strategic turnaround. The telecommunications giant\'s shares rose 4.1% following the announcement.\n\nStay ahead of every breaking move with InvestingPro -- 55% off [...] "We are exiting 2025 with strong momentum, delivered by a team that is intensely focused on winning through healthy volumes and fiscally responsible growth," said Verizon CEO Dan Schulman. "Our performance in the fourth quarter proves that we can grow by delighting our customers and building deep trust and loyalty."\n\nLooking ahead, Verizon provided an optimistic outlook for 2026, projecting adjusted EPS of $4.90 to $4.95, well above the analyst consensus of $4.76. The company expects total retail postpaid phone net additions of 750,000 to 1.0 million and total mobility and broadband service revenue growth of 2.0% to 3.0%.', 'score': 0.99964297, 'raw_content': None}, {'url': 'https://www.tikr.com/blog/verizon-stock-after-a-10-rise-what-the-numbers-say-about-2026', 'title': 'Verizon Stock After a 10% Rise: What the Numbers Say About 2026', 'content': 'Evaluate whether Verizon’s postpaid subscriber momentum can support earnings stability through 2030 using TIKR’s valuation tools →\n\nVerizon Communications Inc. (VZ) provides U.S. wireless and broadband connectivity at national scale, competing primarily on network reliability, pricing discipline, and bundled service depth.\n\nLast week, Verizon Communications Inc. reported $36 billion quarterly revenue and $2 billion net income, confirming stabilization after several uneven operating quarters.\n\nVerizon stock. maintained a 21% operating margin in 2025 as cost controls and restructuring actions offset promotional intensity and elevated capital spending. [...] Following the Frontier acquisition, Verizon Communications Inc. now reaches 30 million fiber locations, supporting subscriber growth targets of 1 million additions in 2026.\n\nWhile Verizon Communications Inc. trades near $45 at 9x earnings, improving fundamentals contrast with restrained valuation, setting up a critical execution-versus-confidence debate.\n\n## What the Model Says for VZ Stock\n\nWe assessed Verizon stock using assumptions tied to fiber expansion, subscriber recovery, and stable cash generation across a mature U.S. telecom base.\n\nBased on 2.3% revenue growth, 24.1% operating margins, and an 8.6x exit multiple, the model implies steady capital returns without valuation expansion. [...] Last updated Feb 3, 2026\n\n### Key Takeaways:\n\n Strategic Expansion: Verizon Communications Inc. completed the Frontier acquisition, expanding fiber reach to 30 million locations, strengthening bundled wireless and broadband positioning.\n Operational Momentum: Verizon Communications Inc. added 616000 postpaid subscribers in Q4, the highest quarterly increase in 6 years, confirming promotional execution.\n Price Framework: Verizon Communications Inc. valuation implies a $60 target by 2028 based on 2% revenue growth, 24% operating margins, and 9x earnings.\n Upside Math: Verizon Communications Inc. offers 35% total upside from $45, translating into a 11% annualized return over 3 years.', 'score': 0.9993538, 'raw_content': None}, {'url': 'https://www.marketbeat.com/stocks/NYSE/VZ/earnings/', 'title': 'Verizon Communications (VZ) Earnings Date and Reports 2026', 'content': "## Verizon Communications Earnings Summary\n\nVerizon Communications released Q4 2025 earnings on January 30, 2026, reporting an EPS of $1.09, which beat analysts' consensus estimates of $1.06 by $0.03. Quarterly revenue rose _2.0%_ year-over-year to $36.38 billion, above analyst estimates of $36.20 billion. With a trailing EPS of _$4.05_ and a P/E Ratio of _12.21_, Verizon Communications' earnings are expected to grow _3.62%_ next year, from $4.69 to $4.86 per share.\n\nUpcoming \n\n Earnings Date Apr. 28 Before Market Opens Estimated\n\nConsensus EPS \n\n (Jan. 30) $1.06 \n\nActual EPS \n\n (Jan. 30) $1.09 Beat By $0.03 \n\nActual Revenue \n\n (Jan. 30) $36.38B\n\n### Q4 2025 Earnings Resources [...] Verizon Communications (NYSE:VZ) has a recorded annual revenue of $138.19 billion.\n\nHow much profit does Verizon Communications generate each year?\n\nVerizon Communications (NYSE:VZ) has a recorded net income of $17.17 billion. VZ has generated $4.05 earnings per share over the last four quarters.\n\nWhat is Verizon Communications' price-to-earnings ratio?\n\nVerizon Communications (NYSE:VZ) has a trailing price-to-earnings ratio of 12.21 and a forward price-to-earnings ratio of 10.54. The price/earnings-to-growth ratio is 2.12.\n\nWhat is Verizon Communications' EPS forecast for next year?\n\nVerizon Communications' earnings are expected to grow from $4.69 per share to $4.86 per share in the next year, which is a 3.62% increase.\n\n## More Earnings Resources from MarketBeat [...] | 4/22/2024 | Q1 2024 | $1.12 | $1.15 | +$0.03 | $1.21 | $33.23B | $33.00B |  |", 'score': 0.9993538, 'raw_content': None}, {'url': 'https://finance.yahoo.com/news/verizon-surpasses-q4-earnings-estimates-145900018.html', 'title': 'Verizon Surpasses Q4 Earnings Estimates on Healthy Revenue ...', 'content': 'In this article:  \n\nVZ\n\n+1.48%\n\nANET\n\n-0.34%\n\nPINS\n\n+0.50%\n\nVerizon Communications Inc. VZ recorded solid fourth-quarter 2025 results with healthy wireless traction and fiber densification. Both adjusted earnings and revenues beat the respective Zacks Consensus Estimate, with the company delivering on its 2025 guidance.   \n  \nThe company registered solid broadband growth with total fixed wireless access net additions of 319,000, growing the subscriber base to nearly 5.7 million. The company remains well poised to achieve its target of 8 to 9 million fixed wireless access subscribers by 2028.\n\n## Net Income [...] ### Verizon Communications Inc. Price, Consensus and EPS Surprise\n\nVerizon Communications Inc. price-consensus-eps-surprise-chart | Verizon Communications Inc. Quote\n\n## Revenues\n\nQuarterly total operating revenues improved 2% to $36.38 billion with higher wireless equipment revenues driven by targeted pricing actions, customer growth, sales of perks and add-on services and growth in fixed wireless access. The top line beat the consensus estimate of $35.94 billion. For 2025, Verizon recorded total revenues of $138.19 billion, up 2.5% year over year.\n\n## Quarterly Segment Results [...] Consumer: Total revenues from this segment improved 3.2% year over year to $28.44 billion with growth across all businesses. Service revenues were up 0.9% to $20.25 billion, while wireless equipment revenues improved 9.6% to $7.11 billion. Other revenues totaled $1.08 billion, up 6.6% year over year.  \n  \nWireless retail postpaid churn was 1.21%, while retail postpaid phone churn was 0.95%. The company recorded 65,000 Fios Internet net additions as high demand for reliable fiber optic broadband was spurred by higher video consumption. Verizon delivered 372,000 broadband net additions in the quarter. However, it registered 53,000 Fios Video net losses in the quarter, reflecting the ongoing shift from traditional linear video to over-the-top offerings.', 'score': 0.99899954, 'raw_content': None}, {'url': 'https://www.verizon.com/about/news/verizon-delivers-2025-financial-guidance-highest-quarterly-net-adds', 'title': 'Verizon Delivers on 2025 Financial Guidance with Highest Quarterly ...', 'content': 'In fourth-quarter 2025, Verizon reported total postpaid phone net additions of 616,000, up from 504,000 in fourth-quarter 2024, marking the best quarter of postpaid phone net additions since 2019.\n Wireless service revenue2 was $21.0 billion in fourth-quarter 2025, up 1.1 percent year-over-year.\n Wireless equipment revenue was $8.2 billion in fourth-quarter 2025, up 9.1 percent year-over-year.\n Verizon delivered 372,000 broadband net additions in fourth-quarter 2025.\n Total fixed wireless access net additions were 319,000 in fourth-quarter 2025, bringing the base to over 5.7 million fixed wireless access subscribers.\n Verizon delivered 67,000 Fios internet net additions in fourth-quarter 2025, the highest fourth-quarter net additions since 2020. [...] Verizon Communications Inc. (NYSE, Nasdaq: VZ) powers and empowers how its millions of customers live, work and play, delivering on their demand for mobility, reliable network connectivity and security. Headquartered in New York City, serving countries worldwide and nearly all of the Fortune 500, Verizon generated revenues of $138.2 billion in 2025. Verizon’s world-class team never stops innovating to meet customers where they are today and equip them for the needs of tomorrow. For more, visit verizon.com or find a retail location at verizon.com/stores\n\n#### Forward-looking statements [...] Total retail postpaid phone net additions of 750,000 to 1.0 million, which is approximately 2 to 3 times the 2025 reported result.\n Total mobility and broadband service revenue growth of 2.0 percent to 3.0 percent, equating to approximately $93 billion. Wireless service revenue growth will be approximately flat in 2026 as the company transitions to sustainable volume-based growth.\n Adjusted EPS1 of $4.90 to $4.95, or year-over-year growth of 4.0 percent to 5.0 percent, representing a significant acceleration compared to recent historical performance.\n Cash flow from operations of $37.5 billion to $38.0 billion.\n Capital expenditures of $16.0 billion to $16.5 billion. This includes a fiber build pace of at least 2.0 million passings in 2026.', 'score': 0.9949397, 'raw_content': None}], 'response_time': 2.45, 'request_id': 'c845a293-767f-4090-92e3-cf29154a7093'}
